It was in this area where he learnt poetry and began busking, outside the Prince of Wales pub, which is now a Tesco Express.|The musician was known for being the founder and leader of psychedelic folk group T. Rex, who produced classics such as|Get it On, Children Of The Revolution|and|I love to Boogie|. He is undoubtedly one of the biggest pop stars of his generation.|The musician and poet sadly died after a car crash in Barnes two weeks before his 30th birthday.
